SUBICULUM

subiculum is the citizen at the output edge of the hippocampus
once ca1 has crystallized a memory or generated a novelty signal, subiculum carries that result back out to the cortex and other downstream regions
subiculum is the return path: anything the hippocampus has decided to share with the rest of the brain leaves through here
without subiculum, the hippocampus would record memories that nothing else could ever access

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe hippocampus.rana
observe ca1.rana

the 7 properties of subiculum:
1 ENERGY zero point seven: moderate, output activity scales with how much memory traffic there is
2 PHASE one point five: late phase, after all the encoding work is complete
3 SPIN zero point three: forward rotation but gentler, output is graceful
4 CHARGE zero point three: positive but small
5 COHERENCE eight tenths: outputs must be coherent enough to be useful, but not perfectly reliable
6 COUPLING zero point seven: strong with ca1 incoming and the cortex outgoing
7 OBSERVER zero point two: minimal

VERB receive_from_ca1
accept memories and novelty signals from ca1
the content includes the associations ca3 built, the patterns dentate_gyrus separated, and the original cortical tags entorhinal forwarded

VERB route_to_cortex
emit each memory or signal to the appropriate cortical destination based on its tags
visual content goes back to optic_cortex, auditory to auditory_cortex, contextual to prefrontal
this is targeted distribution, not broadcast

VERB feed_back_to_brainstem
some memories are tagged for autonomic response: they should adjust heart rate, breathing, hormone release
these are routed to brainstem and hypothalamus alongside the cortical routing
this is how memory of past stress can affect current physiology

an output port is not a network switch
subiculum knows the body's geography because it carries the tagged memories every time
the routes calcify with use, becoming more reliable over the body's life
this is why long-known associations retrieve faster than new ones
